- CHEERS, BABY.         
- CHEERS.               

01:27.420 --> 01:29.255
SO ARE WE GONNA 
TALK ABOUT THAT?

01:29.322 --> 01:32.459
- WHAT?                 
- THAT HANDCUFF         
ON YOUR WRIST.        

01:32.525 --> 01:35.762
JESUS, GIVE ME A BREAK.     
IT'S A BRACELET,            
THAT'S ALL.                 

01:35.829 --> 01:37.564
IT'S CALLED                 
THE LOVE BRACELET           
THOUGH, RIGHT?              

01:37.630 --> 01:39.232
I DON'T KNOW            
WHAT IT'S CALLED.       

01:39.299 --> 01:41.134
THAT'S WHAT IT'S CALLED--       
A CARTIER LOVE BRACELET.        

01:41.167 --> 01:43.670
DOES THIS MEAN      
THAT VINCE AND AMANDA   
ARE IN LOVE?        

01:43.737 --> 01:46.973
, IT MEANS              
E KNOWS WAY TOO MUCH        
ABOUT JEWELRY.          

01:47.040 --> 01:48.675
IS THAT WHAT        
IT'S CALLED, VINCE? 

01:48.742 --> 01:50.677
I DON'T KNOW            
WHAT IT'S CALLED, TURTLE.   

01:50.744 --> 01:52.345
ALL I KNOW IS           
YOU'RE ANNOYING ME.     

01:52.412 --> 01:54.180
<i>AMANDA GOT ME A GIFT,</i>      

01:54.247 --> 01:57.083
<i>A VERY NICE GIFT,</i>      
<i>AND I HAPPEN TO LIKE IT,</i>   
<i>ALL RIGHT?</i>         

01:57.150 --> 01:58.752
SO STAY OFF MY ASS.     

01:58.818 --> 02:01.521
YOU GUYS                    
ARE NOT GONNA BELIEVE       
THE LUCK OF THE IRISH.      

02:01.588 --> 02:04.491
- WE'VE GOT A RE THING      
RUNNING IN THE FIFTH.     
- REALLY?                   

02:04.557 --> 02:05.859
- ARE YOU SERIOUS?          
- HOW DO YOU KNOW, DRAMA?   

02:05.925 --> 02:07.727
BECAUSE I KNOW          
THE PONY'S GRANDDAD.        

02:07.794 --> 02:09.429
<i>AND IN HORSERACING,</i>        
<i>AS IN LIFE,</i>            

02:09.496 --> 02:11.865
A GOOD LINEAGE          
IS THE SUREST WAY       

02:11.931 --> 02:13.700
TO PREDICT          
A FINE PERFORMANCE.     

02:13.767 --> 02:15.335
WELL, HOW COME YOU'RE       
FROM VINCE'S LINEAGE        

02:15.402 --> 02:16.703
AND ALL YOUR            
PERFORMANCES SUCK?      

02:16.770 --> 02:19.939
Vince: ALL RIGHT, JOHNNY,   
WHO'S THE GRANDDADDY?       

02:21.441 --> 02:24.544
KINGMAKER.          
REMEMBER THAT NAME?     

02:24.611 --> 02:25.712
KINGMAKER?          

02:25.779 --> 02:27.213
- NO.                   
- WHO'S THAT?           

02:27.280 --> 02:28.615
<i>COME ON, KING MAKER--</i>      

02:28.715 --> 02:31.017
HE CAME HOME FOR ME     
AT 10 TO ONE AT BELMONT.    

02:31.084 --> 02:34.054
THAT'S HOW          
I BOUGHT THE LINCOLN.       
ANY OF THIS RINGING A BELL? 

02:34.120 --> 02:35.855
- NOT REALLY.           
- NO.                   

02:35.922 --> 02:38.358
I THOUGHT YOU BOUGHT    
YOUR LINCOLN FROM SELLING   
WEED AT THE HIGH SCHOOL.

02:38.425 --> 02:39.959
- THAT RINGS A BELL.        
- WHATEVER.                 

02:40.026 --> 02:42.362
- YOU GUYS WANNA WIN            
SOME DOUGH WITH ME OR NOT?    
- YES.                          

02:42.395 --> 02:43.963
- OBVIOUSLY.            
- DEFINITELY.           

02:44.030 --> 02:46.066
BUT IT'S NOT TILL       
THE FIFTH RACE, SO CAN WE   
DO ANOTHER SHOT?        

02:46.132 --> 02:48.401
YOU GUYS ARE DOING SHOTS        
AT 10:30 IN THE MORNING?    

02:48.468 --> 02:50.403
RELAX, KID.         
IT'S A HOLIDAY.         

02:50.470 --> 02:53.740
- WHAT HOLIDAY IS IT?       
- YOM KIPPUR, RETARD.       

02:53.807 --> 02:55.709
OH YEAH, THAT'S RIGHT.      
I FORGOT.           

02:55.775 --> 02:57.777
NO WONDER THERE WAS     
NO TRAFFIC.         

02:57.844 --> 03:00.880
HEY, CHIEF, CAN WE GET      
COUPLE SHOTS OF CUERVO      
OVER HERE, PLEASE?      

03:00.947 --> 03:02.515
YEAH.       
COMI UP.    

03:02.582 --> 03:04.651
- Sarah: I HATE THIS.       
I'M STARVING.             
- NOW YOU KNOW              

03:04.718 --> 03:06.886
WHAT MOMMY GOES THROUGH         
EVERY DAY TO MAKE               
A HOT BODY FOR DADDY.           

03:06.953 --> 03:09.122
- ARI!                      
- DADDY'S JUST              
KIDDING, SWEETIE.         

03:09.189 --> 03:12.625
SARAH, WE FAST AND  
MAKE OTHER IMPORTANT
SACRIFICES TODAY    

03:12.692 --> 03:15.128
TO SHOW GOD WE'RE SORRY 
FOR OUR SINS.           

03:15.195 --> 03:17.230
- DADDY ATE A BREATH MINT.  
- WHAT?                     

03:17.297 --> 03:19.532
NOW YOU'RE GONNA                
HAVE TO ATONE FOR               
RATTING DADDY OUT, BABY.        

03:19.599 --> 03:21.735
WHAT,  YOU THINK                
GOD WANTS MY BREATH TO SMELL?   

03:21.801 --> 03:25.105
- Man: ARI.                 
- THERE HE IS, LITTLE       
NICKY RUBENSTEIN.         

03:25.171 --> 03:27.107
- SHEILA, HOW ARE YOU?      
GOOD TO SEE YOU.          
- HOW ARE YOU DOING?        

03:27.207 --> 03:28.775
- HAPPY NEW YEAR.           
- WHERE'S THE OLD MAN?      

03:28.842 --> 03:30.477
HE'S ON A PLANE 
TO COLOMBIA.    

03:30.543 --> 03:32.045
ON THE HIGHEST OF HOLIDAYS, 
WOULD YOU BELIEVE?          

03:32.112 --> 03:33.780
MA, STOP.       
WE'VE GOT ENOUGH
STRESS TODAY.   

03:33.847 --> 03:36.549
YOUR FATHER'S GOT               
$100 MILLION IN THE BANK.       
HOW MUCH STRESS CAN YOU HAVE?   

03:36.616 --> 03:38.318
WELL, "MEDALLION"'S         
FALLING APART.              

03:38.385 --> 03:40.420
IT'S "MEDELLIN," MOM.           
WHY THE FUCK CAN'T  
ANYONE PRONOUNCE IT?

03:40.453 --> 03:42.155
- DO NOT CURSE          
IN THE TEMPLE.        
- EXCUSE ME.            

03:42.222 --> 03:44.491
BENICIO WALKED              
AND MY FATHER'S TRYING      
TO PREVENT THE WHOLE CREW   

03:44.557 --> 03:46.860
- FROM DOING THE SAME.          
- HE'S BEEN SAYING BENICIO'S    
GONNA WALK FOR WEEKS.         

03:46.926 --> 03:49.295
NO, IT'S OFFICIAL.      
CHECK OUT "US WEEKLY."  
THERE'S A PICTURE OF HIM

03:49.362 --> 03:51.765
ON A CATAMARAN              
WITH SOME BLONDE BOMBSHELL  
IN ANGUILLA.                

03:51.831 --> 03:54.100
- IT WAS ANTIGUA.           
- ANTIGUA, ANGUILLA--       
WHO THE FUCK CARES?       

03:54.167 --> 03:56.269
- ( all exclaim )           
- ALL RIGHT, EXCUSE ME,     
EXCUSE ME.                

03:56.336 --> 03:58.538
THE POINT IS,           
HAGGIS IS FREAKED, OKAY?

03:58.605 --> 04:00.373
AND GATOFF IS GIVING US 
TILL SUNDOWN TONIGHT    

04:00.440 --> 04:02.308
TO FIND A REPLACEMENT   
OR HE'S GONNA SHUT  
THE WHOLE THING DOWN.   

04:02.375 --> 04:04.611
I HEAR CRUISE IS GOING          
FOR 10Â¢ ON THE DOLLAR.          

04:04.678 --> 04:06.880
NO NO NO NO.            
I WANT YOUR BOY, ARI.   
I WANT VINCE.           

04:06.946 --> 04:09.349
HE'S NOT MY BOY ANYMORE.    
- THEN PUT ME ON THE PHONE  
WITH HIM,                 

04:09.416 --> 04:11.651
'CAUSE THIS GIRL'S      
AGENCY IS CLOSED        
FOR THE FUCKING HOLIDAY.

04:11.718 --> 04:13.887
ARI DOESN'T HAVE A PHONE, NICK. 
IT'S YOM KIPPUR.                

04:13.953 --> 04:16.690
NICK DOESN'T EITHER         
BECAUSE I FRISKED HIM       
BEFORE WE WALKED OUT.       

04:16.755 --> 04:19.325
LOOK, SINCE YOU WON'T   
COMMISSION VINCE ON THIS,   
COMMISSION US, OKAY?    

04:19.426 --> 04:20.860
THE BACK END        
COULD BE HUGE.      

04:20.927 --> 04:22.729
JESUS CHRIST,               
IT IS YOM KIPP.             

04:22.796 --> 04:25.265
AND LOOK WHO JUST               
SAID "JESUS CHRIST."            
YOUR FATHER AGREED TO THIS?     

04:25.331 --> 04:26.933
I KNOW THAT YOU KNOW    
I SPEAK FOR THE FAMILY. 

04:27.000 --> 04:30.437
- NOW COME ON, HELP A FELLOW    
MEMBER OF THE TRIBE.          
- ARI.                          

04:30.503 --> 04:32.505
MY HANDS ARE TIED, NICK.        
I CAN'T DO IT.                  

04:32.572 --> 04:35.508
- NOT TODAY.            
NO BUSINESS.          
- THANK YOU.            

04:41.247 --> 04:43.116
( mouths )                  

04:43.183 --> 04:45.118
50 TO ONE--                     
THAT'S YOUR SURE THING?         

04:45.185 --> 04:47.020
THE BIGGER THE ODDS,    
THE BIGGER THE PAYDAY.  

04:47.087 --> 04:48.922
I'M IN FOR A G. 

04:49.022 --> 04:51.091
A G?  ARE YOU                   
OUT OF YOUR FUCKING MIND?       

04:51.157 --> 04:53.827
- TRUST ME.                 
- I'M PUTTING IN            
FIVE BUCKS, THAT'S IT.    

04:53.893 --> 04:56.096
- YEAH, I'M GOOD FOR 10.    
- PUSSIES.                  

04:56.162 --> 04:57.897
ARE YOU REALLY      
FEELING THIS, JOHNNY?   

04:57.964 --> 05:00.734
YEAH, THEY'RE           
UNDERESTIMATING HIM, BRO,   
JUST LIKE THEY DID HIS GRANDDAD.

05:00.800 --> 05:03.503
AND YOU REMEMBER        
WHAT HE GOT US?         
THE LINCOLN, BABY.      

05:03.536 --> 05:05.672
REMEMBER ALL THE GOOD TIMES 
WE HAD IN THAT CAR?     

05:05.739 --> 05:07.941
FIRST KNICK GAME                
WE EVER WENT TO                 
WAS IN THAT CAR.                

05:08.008 --> 05:11.111
- FIRST GIANTS GAME TOO.    
- FIRST TRIP TO A.C. ALSO.  

05:11.177 --> 05:13.046
WE NEVER TOOK               
THE LINCOLN TO A.C.         

05:13.113 --> 05:14.714
YOU MIGHT HAVE BEEN     
OUT OF TOWN, JOHNNY.    

05:14.781 --> 05:16.716
JESUS CHRIST,       
WHO DROVE?          

05:16.783 --> 05:19.185
( laughs )                      
WHAT'S THE DIFFERENCE?          
COME ON, WE'RE IN.              

05:19.219 --> 05:21.588
WELL, IT'S ONLY MONEY.          
I'M GOOD FOR FIVE Gs.           

05:21.654 --> 05:24.491
- FIVE Gs? ( whistles )     
- WE'RE ALL GONNA GET       
RICH TODAY, BABY.         

05:24.557 --> 05:27.327
BUT LET ME GO FIRST.            
I DON'T WANT YOU GUYS           
FUCKING UP MY ODDS.             

05:27.394 --> 05:29.729
- ( phone rings )       
- LOOK AT THIS.         

05:29.796 --> 05:32.065
WHAT IS THIS,       
A DRUNK DIAL, ARI?  

05:32.132 --> 05:34.801
SORRY, E,               
THE MANISCHEWITZ IS NOT 
FLOWING TILL SUNDOWN.   

05:34.868 --> 05:37.203
- <i>What do you want?</i>         
- I HAVE AN OFFER.          
ARE YOU INTERESTED?       

05:37.270 --> 05:38.605
YEAH.           
CALL OUR AGENT. 

05:38.672 --> 05:40.240
IRONIC THAT ON MY           
PEOPLE'S HOLIDAY            

05:40.306 --> 05:42.075
I'M WORKING                 
AND SHE'S NOT.              
SUCH IS LIFE.               

05:42.142 --> 05:46.913
- SO CALL HER TOMORROW.     
- BENICIO JUST QUIT         
"MEDELLIN" OFFICIALLY.    

05:46.980 --> 05:49.249
<i>They want Vince</i> <i>but th.</i>

05:49.315 --> 05:51.151
- SAYS WHO?             
- PHIL RUBENSTEIN.      

05:51.217 --> 05:53.987
I'M STANDING RIGHT NEXT 
TO HIS SON/CO-PRODUCER  
RIGHT NOW.              

05:54.054 --> 05:56.322
- NICK, SAY HELLO.      
- HELLO, E.             

05:56.389 --> 05:59.059
- HEY, NICK.                
- WE WANT VINCE.            
THIS IS NO BULLSHIT.      

05:59.125 --> 06:01.928
- WHAT'S GOING ON?              
- ARI'S WITH PHIL RUBENSTEIN'S  
SON NICK RIGHT NOW.           

06:01.995 --> 06:03.897
THEY WANT YOU TO DO 
"MEDELLIN."         

06:03.930 --> 06:06.700
THIS IS THE THIRD TIME  
ARI HAS PROMISED YOU    
THIS MOVIE, E.          

06:06.766 --> 06:09.602
- YEAH, BUT THIS TIME IT'S REAL.
- BY THE WAY, THIS IS ALSO      
THE THIRD TIME                

06:09.669 --> 06:11.504
YOU PROMISED ME     
THAT YOU GUYS WOULD 
STOP TALKING TO HIM.

06:11.571 --> 06:13.473
WE'RE NOT TALKING TO HIM.   
WE'RE TALKING TO        
NICK RUBENSTEIN.        

06:13.540 --> 06:15.141
ARI REPRESENTS HIM. 
IT'S NOT FAULT.     

06:15.208 --> 06:16.976
NO, I GUESS NOT.            
BUT I GUESS IT'S MY PROBLEM.

06:17.077 --> 06:18.778
SO WHAT, I'M SUPPOSED TO
JUST SHOW UP AT A TE    

06:18.845 --> 06:21.214
ON THE MOST             
RELIGIOUS DAY OF THE YEAR   
TO DISCUSS BUSINS?      

06:21.281 --> 06:23.616
YOU'RE NOT JUST SHOWING UP. 
THEY'RE EXPECTING YOU.      
THEY'RE GONNA MEET YOU      

06:23.683 --> 06:25.719
IN THE ALLEY                
BEHIND THE SOUTHERN ENTRANCE
NEXT TO THE DUMPSTERS.      

06:25.785 --> 06:28.421
WHAT, SHOULD I                  
BRING A GUN TOO?                
COME ON, ERIC, THIS IS ABSURD.  

06:28.488 --> 06:30.790
- WHAT'S SHE SAYING?        
- SHE DOESN'T WANT          
TO GO TO TEMPLE.          

06:30.857 --> 06:33.026
- LET ME TALK TO HER.       
- SHE'LL GO TEMPLE          
FOR VINCE.                

06:33.126 --> 06:35.962
Drama:                      
SHE'D GO TO THE GAZA STRIP  
IN A YARMULKE FOR VINCE.    

06:36.029 --> 06:38.365
YOU REALIZE THAT THIS           
HAS TO BE LOCKED DOWN           
BY SUNSET, RIGHT?               

06:38.431 --> 06:41.067
YES, ERIC, I HEARD YOU, 
AND I WILL MEET THEM    
ANYWHERE ELSE.          

06:41.134 --> 06:42.969
- AMANDA.               
- PUT VINCE ON.         

06:43.036 --> 06:45.238
- CAN I TALK TO HER?        
- WHY DID YOU WANT ME       
TO CALL HER?              

06:45.305 --> 06:48.475
I DIDN'T WANT YOU TO FEEL       
LEFT OUT OF THE PROCESS.        
COME ON.                        

06:48.541 --> 06:50.143
THIS IS NOT             
A GOOD SITUATION, VINCE.

06:50.210 --> 06:52.712
- HELLO.                
- HEY, VINCE.           

06:52.779 --> 06:54.381
OKAY, IT'S YOM KIPPUR.  
THIS IS RIDICULOUS.     

06:54.447 --> 06:56.383
( laughs )                      
I KNOW, I KNOW.                 

06:56.449 --> 06:58.752
I KNOW.                         

06:58.818 --> 07:01.554
LOOKS LI YOU'RE     
THE THIRD WHEEL NOW,
HUH, E?             

07:01.621 --> 07:04.190
A TINY LITTLE       
SPARE WHEEL.        

07:04.257 --> 07:05.959
OH, THERE HE IS.

07:06.026 --> 07:07.927
WE LOVE YOU, KING!      

07:07.994 --> 07:11.164
- Turtle <i>AW, HE LOOKS</i>           
<i> OUT OF SHAPE.</i>                 
- WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?   

07:11.231 --> 07:13.800
LOOK AT THOSE GLUTES.   
FUCKING BEAUTIFUL.  

07:13.867 --> 07:16.503
DO YOU WANNA                    
WIN MONEY ON HIM                
OR FUCK M, DRAMA?               

07:16.569 --> 07:18.738
DON'T TALK UNCIVILIZED  
AT THE TRACK, E.        

07:18.805 --> 07:20.306
WHAT'D SHE SAY?             

07:20.340 --> 07:22.342
IT'S ALL GOOD.                  
SHE'S HEADING                   
TO TEMPLE NOW.                  

07:22.409 --> 07:24.911
THAT WAS A SURE THING.          

07:24.978 --> 07:26.880
THIS WILL BE        
THE EASIEST PAYCHECK
YOU EVER MADE,      

07:26.946 --> 07:29.015
EXCEPT FOR THAT STINT   
AT SPEARMINT RHINO. 

07:29.082 --> 07:31.751
STOP WASTING TIME, ARI.     
YOU'VE GOT A LOT OF BEGGING 
FOR GOD'S FORGIVENESS       

07:31.818 --> 07:34.120
- TO GO BACK TO.            
- Nick: OKAY, LOOK,         

07:34.187 --> 07:36.122
AMANDA, I SPOKE TO          
THE BIG STUDIO CHIEF        

07:36.189 --> 07:38.458
THIS MORNING, OKAY?         
AND HE'S PREPARED TO MEET   
VINCE'S QUOTE.              

07:38.525 --> 07:39.893
GREAT.  THEN THIS       
SHOULD BE EASY.         

07:39.959 --> 07:41.895
FANTASTIC.              
SO WE'VE GOT A DEAL     
AT THREE MIL.           

07:41.961 --> 07:44.464
UM, NO, BECAUSE VINCE'S         
QUOTE IS SIX MIL.               

07:44.531 --> 07:47.600
- S-SIX?                    
- WHAT'S THE MATTER, ARI,   
SHORT-TERM MEMORY LOSS?   

07:47.701 --> 07:49.703
- ARI, IS IT SIX?           
- YEAH, CK, IT'S SIX.       

07:49.769 --> 07:51.204
I SHOULD KNOW,  
I GOT IT THERE. 

07:51.271 --> 07:53.640
OKAY, ARE WE DOING A DEAL   
OR TALKING ABOUT        
GLORY DAYS?             

07:53.707 --> 07:55.542
I COULD SWEAR                   
MY FATHER SAID                  
IT WAS THREE.                   

07:55.608 --> 07:57.644
WHATEVER.                       
DEAL.  IT'S A DEAL.             
WE'LL DO IT AT SIX.             

07:57.711 --> 07:59.546
GREAT.              
HAVE ARTHUR SIGN OFF,       
CALL ME, AND WE'RE CLOSED.  

07:59.612 --> 08:02.482
DONE.  WE GET VINCE             
ON THE PLANE TONIGHT, DOT THE   
"I's" IN THE MORNING, YES?      

08:02.549 --> 08:03.817
UH, NO.             
ARTHUR CALLS FIRST.     

08:03.883 --> 08:05.652
- UH, AMANDA...         
- ( men laugh )         

08:05.719 --> 08:08.521
...AMANDA, ARTHUR GATOFF        
IS A VERY RELIGIOUS MAN.        
IT'S YOM KIPPUR.                

08:08.588 --> 08:10.857
THE MAN DOESN'T EVEN            
LET HIS KID GO TO LES DEUX      
FRIDAY NIGHT.                  

08:10.924 --> 08:14.060
I GIVE YOU                      
THE RUBENSTEIN FAMILY WORD      
WE HAVE A DEAL AT SIX.          

08:14.127 --> 08:15.729
THE RUBENSTEIN          
FAMILY WORD?            

08:15.795 --> 08:18.064
THAT IS REALLY          
REASSURING, NICK.       

08:18.131 --> 08:19.933
WOW.  OKAY, AMANDA,     
WE'VE CHANGED, ALL RIGHT?   

08:20.000 --> 08:21.601
NEITHER ONE         
OF US HAS HAD A SIP     
IN OVER A YEAR.         

08:21.668 --> 08:23.670
HERE'S MY NUMBER.               
THE PHONE WILL BE ON            
ALL DAY.                        

08:23.737 --> 08:25.672
<i>( engine turns over )</i>          

08:28.508 --> 08:30.477
Sarah:              
<i>MOM TOLD ME TO FIND YOU.</i>   

08:32.479 --> 08:35.215
YODID.                          
I'M IN THE BATHROOM.            
I'M NOT FEELING WELL.           

08:35.280 --> 08:37.350
I'M ON MY HANDS AND KNEE        
I'M VERY SICK RIGHT NOW,        
HONEY.                          

08:37.417 --> 08:39.219
YOU WANT ME TO LIE?!

08:39.284 --> 08:41.020
THAT IS THE BEAUTY              
OF YOM KIPPUR--                 

08:41.087 --> 08:43.957
AS LONG AS YOU                  
APOLOGIZE BY SUNDOWN,           
DOESN'T MATTER WHAT YOU DO.     

08:44.024 --> 08:46.026
NOW GO.                         
I'LL BE BACK SOON.              

08:47.994 --> 08:50.597
WHAT THE FUCK           
ARE WE GONNA DO?        

08:50.663 --> 08:52.432
LET'S GO    
GET GATOFF. 

08:52.499 --> 08:54.668
HE'S AT WILSHIRE ORTHODOX.  
IT'S TWO MILES AWAY.        
YOU GOT A CAR?              

08:54.734 --> 08:56.836
- NO.  YOU?             
- NO.  CALL A CAB?      

08:56.903 --> 08:59.539
- GOT ANY MONEY?            
- NO, MOM TOOK IT.  YOU?    

08:59.606 --> 09:02.275
THE WIFE TOOK EVERYTHING
BUT MY FILLINGS.        

09:02.342 --> 09:03.843
SO WHAT NOW?            

09:03.910 --> 09:06.813
NOW, LIKE OUR           
DESERT-DWELLING ANCESTORS   

09:06.880 --> 09:09.382
WE WALK.    

09:09.449 --> 09:11.384
AW...                           
( mutters )                     

09:12.686 --> 09:15.121
<i>( crowd cheering )</i>     

09:18.024 --> 09:20.760
COME ON!        
YOU'RE THE KING!
GO, BABY, GO!   

09:20.827 --> 09:22.495
EASY, DRAMA.        
HE'S IN LAST.       

09:22.562 --> 09:24.130
SHUT UP, TURTLE.
HE'S PACING     
HIMSELF.        

09:24.197 --> 09:25.865
HE LOOKS LIKE                   
HE'S ON A LEISURE WALK.         

09:25.932 --> 09:28.101
- Vince: <i>OKAY</i>               
- <i>( announcer speaking</i>      
<i> over P.A. )</i>               

09:28.168 --> 09:30.103
SURE YOU CAN TAKE ME            
TO THE AIRPORT.                 

09:30.170 --> 09:32.405
( laughs )                  

09:32.472 --> 09:35.809
<i>YEAH, SOUNDS LIKE</i>              
<i>A GREAT SENDOFF.</i>               

09:35.875 --> 09:37.811
OKAY, BYE.          

09:37.877 --> 09:40.580
IT'S ALL GOOD.          
SHE SAID THE MONEY'S        
NO BIGGIE.          

09:40.647 --> 09:42.949
THEY'RE JUST WAITING        
FOR THE STUDIO HEAD     
TO SIGN OFF.            

09:42.982 --> 09:44.918
- WHAT?             
- NOTHING.          

09:44.984 --> 09:46.986
YOUR GIGGLING'S MAKING ME   
A LITTLE NAUSEOUS.      

09:47.053 --> 09:50.457
GIGGLING?                       
