20:02.669 --> 20:05.438
COOL.               
THE COPS HAVE BEEN  
ASKING EVERYONE.    

20:05.505 --> 20:08.475
EXCUSE ME, OFFICERS,    
IT'S THIS GUS HORSE.    

20:08.541 --> 20:11.378
<i>( police radio chatter )</i>   

20:15.815 --> 20:17.250
CAN WE EAT YET?                 

20:17.317 --> 20:19.486
IN FIVE MINUTES, SHEL,      
YOU CAN EAT TILL YOU DROP.  

20:19.552 --> 20:21.254
OKAY OKAY.                      

20:21.321 --> 20:23.289
EXCUSE ME.          

20:28.828 --> 20:31.131
I'M NOT EVEN MAKING A CALL. 
I'M JUST CHECKING MESSAGES. 

20:31.197 --> 20:33.900
IN FOUR MINUTES, ARI,       
WHEN THE SUN IS DOWN.       

20:33.967 --> 20:35.669
LOOK AT YOUR UNCLE. 

20:36.870 --> 20:39.139
SHELLEY!                    

20:39.205 --> 20:42.075
SORRY SORRY.        
I'M A BAD JEW.      
SHOOT ME.           

20:42.175 --> 20:43.677
HEY, ARI.                       

20:43.743 --> 20:45.712
OH, WILL YOU LOOK   
AT THIS, HUH?   

20:45.779 --> 20:48.548
THE BOYS FROM QUEENS
ARE IN THE MARKET   
FOR SOME BRISKET.   

20:48.615 --> 20:50.316
- SORRY TO BOTHER YOU.          
- WE DON'T MEAN TO INTRUDE.     

20:50.417 --> 20:51.985
WE TRIED TO CALL YOU            
BUT NO ONE WAS ANSWERING.       

20:52.085 --> 20:54.054
WELL, THAT          
WOULD BE MY FAULT.      
I HAVE HIS PHONES.      

20:54.120 --> 20:56.022
WHAT'S UP?  

20:56.089 --> 20:57.924
- WE'RE IN, ARI.            
- WHATEVER IT TAKES.        
JUST TELL US              

20:57.991 --> 21:00.593
- HOW TO GET AHOLD OF NICK.     
- THAT'S EASY.                  
YOU GOT A PHONE?              

21:05.131 --> 21:07.000
WHAT?               
THEY'RE NOT JEWISH. 

21:10.970 --> 21:12.939
<i>( phone ringing )</i>      

21:14.407 --> 21:16.343
Sheila:             
<i>DON'T YOU DARE</i>         
<i>ANSWER THAT PHONE, NICK.</i>   

21:16.409 --> 21:18.545
HEY!                
MY LIFE IS FALLING APART!   

21:18.611 --> 21:20.347
I HAVEN'T EATEN         
IN 10 HOURS!            

21:20.413 --> 21:22.415
SO GET OFF MY ASS!      

21:22.482 --> 21:24.417
<i>( phone continues ringing )</i>    

21:25.618 --> 21:27.587
I'M SORRY.          
I'M SORRY.          

21:29.155 --> 21:31.291
- HELLO.                    
- NICK, I'M STANDING        
HERE WITH VINCE.          

21:31.358 --> 21:32.792
- HEY, NICK.            
- HE'S IN.              

21:32.859 --> 21:34.427
I'M IN, NICK.       
WHATEVER YOU NEED.  

21:34.494 --> 21:36.196
Ari:                
<i>He'll jump</i>         
<i>on a plane tonight,</i>        

21:36.262 --> 21:38.498
<i>lo deal down tomorrow</i>      
<i>if everyone agrees</i>     
<i>to be fair.</i>            

21:38.531 --> 21:40.633
YEAH, WELL,         
LIFE'S NOT FAIR, GUYS.      

21:40.700 --> 21:42.802
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?   

21:42.869 --> 21:46.506
IT'S OVER.          
IT'S OVER.          
THE SUN HAS SET.        

21:46.539 --> 21:48.641
- WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?   
- WE'VE STILL GOT TWO MINUTES.  

21:48.708 --> 21:51.144
- WE'RE GOOD TO GO.         
- HE PULLED THE PLUG, ARI.  

21:51.211 --> 21:53.013
GATOFF YANKED IT RIGHT      
OUT OF THE FUCKING WALL.    

21:53.079 --> 21:55.315
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN, NICK?   
- I MEAN IT'S GONE.         

21:55.382 --> 21:57.083
ERIC, IT'S GONE.        
THE MOVIE IS GONE       

21:57.150 --> 21:59.052
AND THERE'S NOTHING     
I CAN DO ABOUT IT.      

22:00.820 --> 22:03.390
6:58.                           
EVERYBODY CAN EAT.              

22:03.456 --> 22:06.526
THANKS, I LOST  
MY APPETITE.    

22:06.559 --> 22:08.962
$5000 BUCKS                     
FOR NOT HAVING A PERMIT.        

22:09.029 --> 22:11.064
THAT'S TWICE WHAT I PAID        
FOR THE BIG BOY.                

22:11.131 --> 22:13.600
AND YOU'RE GONNA KEEP   
GETTING TICKETS, DRAMA. 

22:13.667 --> 22:16.069
YOU GOTTA GIVE  
THIS GUY BACK.  

22:16.136 --> 22:18.171
THEY'LL SEND HIM                
TO THE GLUE FACTORY, TURTLE.    

22:18.238 --> 22:20.006
NO GO.              

22:20.073 --> 22:22.008
WE GOTTA FIND HIM       
A GOOD HOME.            

22:22.075 --> 22:24.344
DO YOU KNOW ANYONE      
THAT'S GOT HORSES?      

22:24.411 --> 22:27.414
YOU KNOW EVERYONE   
I KNOW, DRAMA.  NO. 

22:29.549 --> 22:31.418
I GOT AN IDEA.          

22:31.518 --> 22:33.153
OH, THIS DOESN'T
SOUND GOOD.     

22:33.219 --> 22:35.722
OH NO, IT'S GOOD.       
IT'S VERY GOOD          

22:35.755 --> 22:38.358
FOR MY HORSE            
AND MY CAREER.          
COME, BOY.  COME ON, KING.  

22:38.425 --> 22:40.760
- WHERE ARE YOU GOING?      
- HELP ME GET HIM           
IN THE TRAILER.           

22:42.095 --> 22:44.664
GUYS, I KNOW HOW MUCH           
YOU WANTED THIS,                
AND AS A FRIEND                 

22:44.731 --> 22:47.000
I CAN ONLY SAY                  
I'M SORRY.                      

22:47.100 --> 22:49.035
- THANKS.               
- THANKS, ARI.          

22:49.102 --> 22:52.439
HEY, YOU KNOW,          
AND THANKS FOR NOT BASHING  
AMANDA DURING THIS.     

22:52.539 --> 22:54.341
I KNOW YOU'VE BEEN      
DYING TO.           

22:54.407 --> 22:56.409
I THINK THE SITUATION           
SPEAKS FOR ITSELF.              

22:56.476 --> 22:58.878
- ARI.                  
- SORRY SORRY.          

23:00.580 --> 23:02.682
- SEE YOU, ARI.         
- GOOD NIGHT.           

23:04.451 --> 23:06.353
HE WOULD HAVE NEVER             
LET THIS HAPPEN.                

23:06.419 --> 23:08.955
NO, HE WOULDN'T HAVE.   
SO WHAT NOW?        

23:09.022 --> 23:10.957
NOW I DEAL WITH IT.             

23:11.024 --> 23:13.259
TAKE ME TO THE RESTAURANT.  

23:13.326 --> 23:15.962
( rings doorbell )      

23:19.466 --> 23:21.201
HEY, EDDIE.                     

23:21.267 --> 23:23.036
HEY, JOHNNY.    
WHAT'S UP?      

23:23.103 --> 23:25.472
SORRY TO BOTHER YOU.            
I HOPE YOU'RE NOT               
IN THE MIDDLE OF DINNER.        

23:25.538 --> 23:29.642
NO NO, WE JUST FINISHED.
BUT HOW DID YOU GET     
MY ADDRESS?             

23:29.709 --> 23:32.145
GOOD ONE, EDDIE.                
BUT I'VE BEEN HERE BEFORE.      

23:32.212 --> 23:34.014
HAVE YOU?           

23:34.080 --> 23:36.716
HAVEN'T I?                  

23:36.783 --> 23:39.753
WHAT'S GOING ON?    
ARE YOU NERVOUS     
ABOUT THE PREMIERE? 

23:39.819 --> 23:42.122
LOOK, PEOPLE ARE GONNA WATCH,   
TRUST ME, ALL RIGHT?        

23:42.188 --> 23:44.157
NO NO, I FEEL GOOD              
ABOUT THAT.                     

23:44.224 --> 23:46.760
I JUST CAME BY                  
TO SAY THANK YOU                

23:46.826 --> 23:48.995
'CAUSE I OWE YOU                
BIG TIME FOR THIS ONE.          

23:49.095 --> 23:51.231
- AND I WON'T LET YOU DOWN. 
- THAT'S GOOD, THAT'S GOOD. 

23:51.297 --> 23:52.932
I APPRECIATE THAT,  
ALL RIGHT?          

23:52.999 --> 23:55.802
AND I BROUGHT YOU A GIFT        
AS A TOKEN OF MY                
APPRECIATION.                   

23:55.835 --> 23:57.671
- A GIFT?               
- YEEAH.                

23:57.771 --> 24:00.006
COME HERE.                      
YOU'RE GONNA LOVE IT.           

24:00.106 --> 24:02.409
- TURTLE!               
- ( King neighs )       

24:03.910 --> 24:07.147
YOU BOUGHT ME A HORSE?  

24:07.213 --> 24:10.050
<i>YEAH, WELL, I THOUGHT</i>          
<i>SINCE YOU HAVE</i>                 
<i>SMALL KIDS...</i>                  

24:10.116 --> 24:12.619
ARE YOU OUT                 
OF YOUR FUCKING MIND?       
THIS IS BEVERLY HILLS.      

24:12.686 --> 24:14.454
WHAT AM I GONNA DO      
WITH A HORSE?           

24:14.521 --> 24:16.623
OH MY GOD,              
A HORSE!                

24:16.690 --> 24:19.793
IS THAT FOR MY BIRTHDAY?    
HE'S SO BEAUTIFUL!          

24:19.859 --> 24:22.262
Eddie:              
<i>THANK YOU, MAN.</i>        

24:22.328 --> 24:24.197
NICE.               

24:29.536 --> 24:32.505
DO YOU WANT ME      
TO GO IN WITH YOU?  

24:32.539 --> 24:34.507
NO, I GOT IT.                   

24:34.541 --> 24:38.211
BUT WAIT.                       
IT'LL BE QUICK.                 

24:48.655 --> 24:51.624
( sighs )                   
I'M SORRY, VINCE.           

24:51.691 --> 24:53.059
ARE YOU?            

24:53.126 --> 24:54.894
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?            

24:54.961 --> 24:58.231
IT MEANS, AMANDA,   
I CHASED THIS MOVIE 
FOR TWO YEARS       

24:58.331 --> 25:00.500
HARDER THAN I'VE CHASED 
ANYTHING IN MY LIFE     

25:00.567 --> 25:02.369
AND I WANTED IT SO BADLY.   

25:02.402 --> 25:04.237
I KNOW, VINCE,                  
AND I WANTED IT FOR YOU.        

25:04.304 --> 25:07.073
- IT DOESN'T FEEL THAT WAY.     
- NO?  HOW DOES IT FEEL?        

25:07.173 --> 25:10.210
IT FEELS LIKE YOU STALLED.  
AND I'M JUST WONDERING,     

25:10.243 --> 25:13.146
<i>ARE YOU STALLING AS MY AGENT</i>   
<i>BECAUSE YOU DON'T</i>          
<i>LIKE THE PROJECT</i>           

25:13.213 --> 25:15.648
OR AS MY GIRLFRIEND 

25:15.715 --> 25:18.551
BECAUSE YOU DON'T LIKE  
THE IDEA THAT I'LL BE   
GONE FOR SIX MONTHS?    

25:18.585 --> 25:20.587
ARI CONVINCED YOU               
THAT I STALLED?                 

25:20.653 --> 25:23.623
I LOST A PROJECT.       
WHAT DIFFERENCE DOES    
IT MAKE WHO IT WAS?     

25:23.723 --> 25:25.892
THE DIFFERENCE IS,              
YOU HAVE NEVER LET ARI          

25:25.959 --> 25:28.561
WELL, MAYBE         
I SHOULDN'T HAVE.   

25:28.595 --> 25:31.231
NO, MAYBE YOU               
SHOULDN'T HAVE.             

25:31.297 --> 25:32.866
BUT LET ME JUST             
TELL YOU THIS:              

25:32.932 --> 25:35.235
I DIDN'T LOSE THE MOVIE.        
THE MOVIE WAS LOST              

25:35.301 --> 25:37.537
WHEN NICK RUBENSTEIN BARGED     
INTO ARTHUR GATOFF'S TEMPLE     

25:37.604 --> 25:39.539
FOR THE SECOND TIME             
THIS AFTERNOON                  

25:39.606 --> 25:41.574
<i>LIKE THE SPOILED</i>               
<i>LITTLE BABY HE IS.</i>             

25:41.608 --> 25:43.543
NOW ARTHUR PAYS PEOPLE          
TO MAKE HIS LIFE EASIER,        

25:43.610 --> 25:45.578
BUT TODAY                       
NICK DIDN'T DO THAT.            

25:45.612 --> 25:47.580
INSTEAD, HE AGGRAVATED          
HIM EVEN MORE.                  

25:47.614 --> 25:50.383
AND I KNOW THIS                 
BECAUSE ARTHUR CALLED ME        
RIGHT AFTER SUNDOWN.            

25:50.450 --> 25:54.120
<i>AND YOU KNOW WHAT HE SAID?</i>     
<i>"THIS MOVIE WAS PLAGUED</i>        
<i>SINCE DAY ONE.</i>                 

25:54.187 --> 25:56.923
I'M GONNA CUT MY LOSSES.        
BUT I LOVE VINCE.               

25:56.956 --> 25:59.192
I'D LOVE TO DO JUST ABOUT       
ANYTHING ELSE WITH HIM.         

25:59.259 --> 26:01.795
<i>LET'S SET A LUNCH."</i>            

26:04.130 --> 26:07.467
I FEEL STUPID.  

26:07.534 --> 26:09.936
PROBABLY DOESN'T HAPPEN         
TO YOU A LOT, HUH?              

26:09.969 --> 26:11.905
( chuckles )    

26:14.874 --> 26:17.143
SO WHAT DO WE DO NOW?   

26:18.411 --> 26:21.314
VINCE,                     
WE SAY GOODBYE.             

